This paper discusses machine learning algorithms and their ability to adapt to new data presented serially over time. It also discusses the concept of transfer learning, which is commonly used in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Given these topics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the potential for embodied learning, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
